# Charlotte County Solar Permits — Live Map

Scrapes the [Charlotte County BOCC Accela Citizen Access portal](https://aca-prod.accela.com/BOCC/Cap/CapHome.aspx?module=Building&TabName=Building) for solar permits across all statuses, geocodes the addresses, and plots them on a color-coded interactive map.

## What it does

- Searches three solar license types: `C SOLAR ENERGY`, `C SOLAR SYSTEM`, `C SOLAR WAT HEAT`
- Pulls the last 365 days of permits
- Geocodes each address with OpenStreetMap Nominatim (free, cached)
- Saves results to `permits.json`
- The map app loads `permits.json` and displays markers color-coded by status

## Color legend

| Status | Color |
|---|---|
| Issued / Approved | teal-green |
| In Review | amber |
| Submitted | blue |
| Pending | purple |
| Finaled / Closed | emerald |
| On Hold | orange |
| Expired | red |
| Void / Withdrawn | gray |
| Other | lavender |

## How it stays updated

A GitHub Action (`.github/workflows/refresh.yml`) runs the scraper every day at 11:00 UTC and commits any changes to `permits.json`. The map served via GitHub Pages picks up the new data automatically.

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `scraper.py` | Scrapes Accela + geocodes; writes `permits.json` |
| `index.html` | Single-file map app (Leaflet + dark CARTO tiles) |
| `permits.json` | Generated data file |
| `.geocode_cache.json` | Geocoded address cache (auto-managed) |
| `.github/workflows/refresh.yml` | Daily refresh CI job |

## Source

All data is sourced from public records on the Charlotte County, FL Board of County Commissioners Accela Citizen Access portal.
